# Sentinel Shield — Semgrep scope for React / front-end projects.
# Copy to your repository ROOT as `.semgrepignore`. The Sentinel Shield workflows
# run Semgrep with `-w /src` so this file (at the repo root) is honored.
#
# SCOPE: SEMGREP / SAST ONLY. It does NOT change:
#   npm audit · Trivy (fs/deps) · Syft SBOM · Gitleaks · composer audit · Hadolint
# Those still scan dependencies, lockfiles, and the whole tree.
# (See docs/semgrep-scoping.md.)
#
# Goal: scan application source (src/, app/, components/, resources/js); do NOT
# treat installed deps or build output as application code.

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build / bundler output
dist/
build/
coverage/
.next/
out/
.svelte-kit/
.turbo/
storybook-static/

# If colocated with a PHP/Laravel backend (monorepo), these are not app source:
vendor/
storage/
public/build/
public/vendor/

# Do NOT exclude your application source — keep src/ and resources/js scanned.
